metadata.title: World Ocean Circulation Experiment: P15N hydrographic section of the Pacific Ocean from Dutch Harbor, Alaska to American Samoa
metadata.description: In 1994, the J.P. Tully sailed from Dutch Harbor, Alaska to American Samoa (15 degrees south) along 165W (line P15N).  More than 3300 sea water samples were collected and analyzed for a variety of parameters which were intended to help describe ocean circulation. The World Ocean Circulation Experiment (WOCE) is an international experiment conceived to provide the first comprehensive global survey of physical properties of the oceans.
keywords: Northeast Pacific and the Gulf of Alaska
metadata.notes:
Purpose: The resulting World Ocean Circulation Experiment (WOCE) data sets will be used to test computer models of the ocean circulation needed for predicting decadal climate change.

Supplemental Information: Physical samples exist for this dataset. Custom software is available for use with this dataset.
